count_cols = ['Area Type', 'City', 'Furnishing Status', 'Tenant Preferred', "Bathroom", 'Point of Contact', "BHK"] 
fig, axs = plt.subplots(4, 2, figsize=(20, 22), sharey=True)
axs = axs.flatten()
for i, col in enumerate(count_cols):
    sns.countplot(x=col, data=train, ax=axs[i])
    axs[i].set_title(f'Countplot of {col}')
    axs[i].set_xlabel(col)
    axs[i].set_ylabel('Count')
    for p in axs[i].patches:
        axs[i].annotate(f'{p.get_height()}', (p.get_x() + p.get_width() / 2., p.get_height()), 
                        ha='center', va='center', xytext=(0, 10), textcoords='offset points')
for i in range(len(count_cols), len(axs)):
    axs[i].axis('off')
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

In[]:
house["Floor House"] = house["Floor"].str.split(" ").str.get(0)
house["Floor Building"] = house["Floor"].str.split(" ").str.get(-1)
house.drop("Floor", axis=1, inplace=True)
house.loc[house["Floor House"] == "Ground", "Floor House"] = 0
house.loc[house["Floor Building"] == "Ground", "Floor Building"] = 0
house.loc[house["Floor House"] == "Lower", "Floor House"] = 0
house.loc[house["Floor House"] == "Upper", "Floor House"] = house.loc[house["Floor House"] == "Upper", "Floor Building"]
house["Floor House"] = house["Floor House"].astype(int) 
house["Floor Building"] = house["Floor Building"].astype(int)

count_cols = ['Area Type', 'City', 'Furnishing Status', 'Tenant Preferred', 'Bathroom', 'Point of Contact', 'BHK']
fig, axs = plt.subplots(4, 2, figsize=(20, 22))
for i, col in enumerate(count_cols):
    r_i = i // 2
    c_i = i % 2
    ax = axs[r_i][c_i]
    sns.kdeplot(data=train, x='Rent', hue=col, 
                cumulative=True, ax=ax, warn_singular=False, linewidth=3, common_norm=False) 
    ax.set(xlabel="Rent", ylabel=f"Count ({col})")
    sns.despine(ax=ax, left=True)
    ax.grid(axis='y', linewidth=0.2)
   
if len(count_cols) % 2 != 0:
    fig.delaxes(axs[-1, -1])

plt.show()

dummy_df = pd.get_dummies(house,columns=['Area Type',	'City',	'Furnishing Status',	'Tenant Preferred',	'Point of Contact'],dtype=int)
scaler = StandardScaler()
numerical_cols = ['BHK','Rent', 'Size', 'Bathroom', 'Floor House', 'Floor Building']
#      
train_d, test_d, = train_test_split(dummy_df, random_state=1, test_size=0.25)
#      ,   
scaler.fit(train_d)
train_d[numerical_cols] = scaler.fit_transform(train_d[numerical_cols])
test_d[numerical_cols] = scaler.transform(test_d[numerical_cols])
train_df, val_df = train_test_split(train_d, random_state=1, test_size=0.2)  
X_train = train_df.drop('Rent', axis=1)
y_train = train_df['Rent']
X_val = val_df.drop('Rent', axis=1)
y_val = val_df['Rent']
X_test = test_d.drop('Rent', axis=1)
y_test = test_d['Rent']
In[]:
from sklearn.model_selection import  GridSearchCV
from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestRegressor
from sklearn.metrics import mean_squared_error, r2_score
random.seed(1)
rf_model = RandomForestRegressor(random_state=1)
#       
param_grid = {
    'n_estimators': [ 150, 200,250],
    'max_depth': [ 15,20,30],
    'min_samples_split': [ 5,10,15],
    'min_samples_leaf': [1, 2, 4]
}
#    MSE 'neg_'    metrics.mean_squared_error          _neg
#'neg_mean_squared_error'  MSE
grid_search = GridSearchCV(estimator=rf_model, param_grid=param_grid, scoring='neg_mean_squared_error', cv=5, n_jobs=-1)
#       
grid_search.fit(X_train, y_train)
print("Best Parameters:", grid_search.best_params_)
best_rf_model = grid_search.best_estimator_
#     
y_train_pred = best_rf_model.predict(X_train)
mse_train_rf = mean_squared_error(y_train, y_train_pred)
r2_train_rf = r2_score(y_train, y_train_pred)
print(f'Train Mean Squared Error: {mse_train_rf:.4f}')
print(f'Train R-squared: {r2_train_rf:.4f}')
#     
y_test_pred_rf = best_rf_model.predict(X_test)
mse_test_rf = mean_squared_error(y_test, y_test_pred_rf)
r2_test_rf = r2_score(y_test, y_test_pred_rf)
print(f'Test Mean Squared Error: {mse_test_rf:.4f}')
print(f'Test R-squared: {r2_test_rf:.4f}')

from sklearn.ensemble import GradientBoostingRegressor

from sklearn.ensemble import AdaBoostRegressor

#    
gb_model = GradientBoostingRegressor(n_estimators=100, learning_rate=0.1, random_state=1)

#     
gb_model.fit(X_train, y_train)

#     
y_val_pred = gb_model.predict(X_val)
mse_val = mean_squared_error(y_val, y_val_pred)
r2_val = r2_score(y_val, y_val_pred)

print(f'Validation GradientBoosting Mean Squared Error: {mse_val:.4f}')
print(f'Validation GradientBoosting R-squared: {r2_val:.4f}')

# 
adaboost_model = AdaBoostRegressor(n_estimators=100, learning_rate=0.1, random_state=1)

r2_val = r2_score(y_val, y_val_pred)

# Convert pandas DataFrames to PyTorch tensors
import torch.nn as nn
import torch.optim as optim
from torch.utils.data import DataLoader, TensorDataset
torch.manual_seed(1)
X_train_tensor = torch.tensor(X_train.values, dtype=torch.float32)
y_train_tensor = torch.tensor(y_train.values,dtype=torch.float32).view(-1, 1) # Reshape for a single output
X_val_tensor = torch.tensor(X_val.values, dtype=torch.float32)
y_val_tensor = torch.tensor(y_val.values, dtype=torch.float32).view(-
1, 1) # Reshape for a single output
# Create DataLoader for training and testing datasets
train_dataset = TensorDataset(X_train_tensor, y_train_tensor)
val_dataset = TensorDataset(X_val_tensor, y_val_tensor)
batch_size = 64
train_loader = DataLoader(train_dataset, batch_size=batch_size,
shuffle=True)
test_loader = DataLoader(val_dataset, batch_size=batch_size,
shuffle=False)
# Define a simple neural network model
class RegressionModel(nn.Module):
      def __init__(self, input_size):
        super(RegressionModel, self).__init__()
        self.fc1 = nn.Linear(input_size, 128)
        self.relu = nn.ReLU()
        self.dropout = nn.Dropout(0.25)  #   Dropout  
        self.fc2 = nn.Linear(128, 64)
        self.fc3 = nn.Linear(64, 1)

      def forward(self, x):
        x = self.fc1(x)
        x = self.relu(x)
        x = self.dropout(x)
        x = self.fc2(x)
        x = self.relu(x)
        x = self.dropout(x)
        x = self.fc3(x)
        return x

# Instantiate the model
input_size = X_train.shape[1]
model = RegressionModel(input_size)

# Define loss function and optimizer
criterion = nn.MSELoss()
optimizer = optim.Adam(model.parameters(), lr=0.001)
early_stopping_patience = 15  # Number of epochs to wait for improvement
best_val_loss = float('inf')
current_patience = 0
# Training loop
num_epochs = 100
for epoch in range(num_epochs):
    model.train()
    for batch_X, batch_y in train_loader:
        optimizer.zero_grad()
        outputs = model(batch_X)
        loss = criterion(outputs, batch_y)
        loss.backward()
        optimizer.step()

    # Evaluate on training set
    model.eval()
    with torch.no_grad():
        train_predictions = model(X_train_tensor)
        train_loss = criterion(train_predictions, y_train_tensor)
        r2_trainnn = r2_score(y_train_tensor.numpy(),train_predictions.numpy())

    # Evaluate on val set
    with torch.no_grad():
        val_predictions = model(X_val_tensor)
        val_loss = criterion(val_predictions, y_val_tensor)
        r2_test = r2_score(y_val_tensor.numpy(),val_predictions.numpy())
    
    if val_loss < best_val_loss:
        best_val_loss = val_loss
        current_patience = 0
    else:
        current_patience += 1
        if current_patience >= early_stopping_patience:
            print(f'Early stopping after {epoch+1} epochs')
            break
    # Print training and testing metrics for every epoch
    print(f'Epoch [{epoch+1}/{num_epochs}], Train Loss: {train_loss.item():.4f}, Val Loss: {val_loss.item():.4f}, R-squared: {r2_test:.4f}')
    
X_test_tensor = torch.tensor(X_test.values, dtype=torch.float32)
y_test_tensor = torch.tensor(y_test.values, dtype=torch.float32).view(-1, 1)

# Final evaluation on the test set
model.eval()
with torch.no_grad():
    final_test_predictions = model(X_test_tensor)
    final_test_loss = criterion(final_test_predictions, y_test_tensor)
    final_r2_test = r2_score(y_test_tensor.numpy(), final_test_predictions.numpy())

print(f'Final Test Loss: {final_test_loss.item():.4f}, Final R-squared: {final_r2_test:.4f}')
